The paper proposes a deep reinforcement learning algorithm for robot control, which suggests that it could belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The algorithm is based on the Soft Actor-Critic (SAC) algorithm, which is a popular deep reinforcement learning algorithm in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of a discriminator and a guider, which are commonly used in Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and could suggest a connection to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper focuses on improving the exploration efficiency of the algorithm, which could suggest a connection to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
